We managed to let the car follow a road, where we can set the speed and let the car move past the same point several times. We have also plotted a pedestrian here. The next step is to figure out how to play with 2 players at the same time because then we can actually simulate the experiment.

We made a new modified road and managed to get the car driving automaticaly drinving on that road using these coordinates:

coordinates/rotati/scale of road:
    X: 620 Y:0 Z: 0
    X: -90  Y:0 Z:0
    X: 0.6 Y:20 Z: 1
WP1:coordinates
    X: 620 Y:0 Z:-100
WP2:coordinates
    X: 620 Y:0 Z:-200
WP3:coordinates
    X: 620 Y:0 Z:-300
WP4:coordinates
    X: 620 Y:0 Z:-400
Car Spawn coordinates:
    X: 620 Y:0 Z:0

This is how to make self driving car self driving:
    Go to prefabs/cars go to driveable smart, click it, in inspector 
    go to player avatar and then set type to pedestrian        

The case of something going wrong: 
    - then the car has to decide to hit the pedestrian 
    - or go offroad, 
    - or stay behind the pedestrian going 1,2km/h per hour.

