Week 6
---------------------
Regarding the experiments that we will perform, we defined  a set of vehicle velocities and distances between the vehicle and the pedestrian so that we can conduct our experiment.
+-------------+--------------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+
|             | Velocities   | 5 km/h  | 10 km/h | 15 km/h | 20 km/h | 30 km/h | 40 km/h | 50 km/h | 75 km/h | 
+-------------+--------------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+
| Distances   |Comfort/Safety|         |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |
+-------------+--------------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+
| 0.5 m       |              |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |
+-------------+--------------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+
| 1 m         |              |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |         | 
+-------------+--------------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+
| 1.5 m       |              |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |
+-------------+--------------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+
| 2 m         |              |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |
+-------------+--------------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+
| 3 m         |              |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |         |
+-------------+--------------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+

Note that this values are only our initial guesses and will change during the course of the actual experiment.
On each cell, one of three values would be inputted to classify the pedestrian's interaction with the vehicle:
- Comfortable and Safe
- Not Comfortable but Safe
- Not Comfortable, not Safe

To mitigate the somewhat subjective nature of this experiment, each group member will take turns controlling the civilian and the level of Comfort / Safety will be the mode of each member's assessment.

